---

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{600%g}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks).

Add the potatoes to the boiling water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} or @?water{}. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and halved lengthways, no need to peel, chopped into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @mushrooms{150%g}(roughly chopped).

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once the pan is hot, add the carrot and @baby carrots{150%g} and fry for ~{5-6%mins}.

Stir in the garlic, lower heat to medium and cook for ~{1%min}.

Add a splash of water and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}.

Cook until the veg is tender, ~{4-5%mins}. Remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to high heat with another drizzle of oil.

Season the @21 Day Aged Irish Sirloin Steak{250%g} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the pan is hot, fry the sirloin until browned, ~{1-2%mins} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%mins} on each side if you want it more well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest, ~{1-2%mins}.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with @butter{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Once melted, fry the @dried thyme{1%sachet} and mushrooms for ~{3-4%mins}.

Add @flour{1%tsp} (double for 4p) and fry for ~{30%seconds}. Pour in @water{75%ml} (double for 4p) and bring to the boil. Cook until thickened, ~{1-2%mins}.

Once cooked, remove from the heat and stir in the @truffle oil{1%pack}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice the steak and divide between #plates{}.

Serve the mash and garlicky veg alongside.

Sprinkle the @grated Italian Style Hard Cheese{1%sachet} over the pan-fried veg.

Drizzle the mushroom sauce over the steak.